# This file keeps the logs/ directory tracked by Git.
# 
# WHY?
#   Git doesn't track empty directories. Our pipeline writes log files here,
#   but the directory itself needs to exist. Without this file, a fresh Git
#   clone would be missing the logs/ directory and the pipeline would error
#   when trying to write logs/pipeline.log.
#
# The .gitignore file is configured to track this file but ignore *.log files
# inside the directory — so the directory structure is preserved without
# committing actual log content to the repo.
